@NODE "M01" "Introduction"

I·N·T·R·O·D·U·C·T·I·O·N
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
TagMySig (Herein known as `TMS'), will add a random tagline to
your YAM .signature file. Well, you may ask, `what is the point in
that?' Well, in YAM2P6 the tagline system doesn`t seem to work.
There are probably already tonnes of these programs lying around,
TMS has the following features:

 o Works perfectly with YAM2P6!
 o Reads a random tagline from any size file in well under a second!
 o Can specify your .taglines and .signature file.
 o Comes with 2 AREXX scripts ready to use in YAM.
 o Can tag specific lines of your signature.
 o Can specify Prefixs. So if you have sigs that use: `<sb>' or `<tsb>'
   for Separator bars in YAM, you can also use the Prefixing to
   add `TAGLINE: ' or `    ' indents to the front of your taglines.
 o Comes complete with the source-code (Blitz).
 o CLI program, 17K, and can be installed a number of different ways.
 
I wasn`t going to release TMS, but I`ve heard of so many poeple
having problems with Taglines in YAM, that I thought I should anyway.

Happy tagging...

@ENDNODE

