@NODE "M10" "Using the CLI program."

C·L·I··U·S·A·G·E
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
The CLI program `TMS' (Which should be located in C: after you
run the installer) has the following arguments:

 TMS <TagLines_File> <Signature_File> <Strip_Line> [<Prefix_Text>]

TAGLINES_FILE:
  The path of your Taglines file ("YAM:.taglines"?) enclosed in
  quotes.

SIGNATURE_FILE:
  The path of your Signature file {"YAM:.signature"?} enclosed in
  quotes.

STRIP_LINE:
  The line number in your sig to replace with the random tagline.
  You MUST remember that line number 1 is actually 0, so if your
  signature file was:

  0: Mr Nobble, Contacting me:
  1: mrnobble@aol.com | IRC: irc.ais.com (#AmiGames)
  2:  
  3: WE WANT OUR TAG HERE
  4:
  5: Have a nice day.

  You would specify "3" for the Strip_Line parameter.

PREFIXTEXT:
  This is optional! It will cause TMS to prefix your random
  tagline with the Text you specify. IE, if you specify "TAG: "
  as the Prefix_Text, your sig-tagline would read something like:
  
  TAG: 3 types of people: Those who can count, and those who cant.

  This means that you can use "<sb>" and "<tsb>", to put your tagline
  inside a separator bar :)


Use `TMS ?' to get the options.
 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "M11" "TagLines file"

T·A·G·L·I·N·E·S··F·I·L·E
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
The taglines file you specify, should be formatted it 1 line taglines,
IE:

Where did the Tag go?
Be wery wery quite, Im hunting tagwines!
   
You get the picture? Because TMS picks a random line from the tagline
file, so you cant have multiple line tags.

To get tagline files, check your local BBS, or do a search on AmiNet
for `Tag' or `Taglines'.. There are litterally MILLIONS of them 
around!

@ENDNODE



@NODE "I00" "Editing the Scripts."

E·D·I·T·I·N·G··T·H·E··S·C·R·I·P·T·S
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
You can edit the scripts with a standard Text Editor, such as
CED/BED/GED/ED/TED

We assume by this point, you have used the installer and the 2
AREXX scripts are located in: YAM:REXX/
(`TMS.yam' and `MULTI_TMS.yam')

And the Change_Tagline program is still in your TMS/ directory.

If you are using Installation method 1, you will only need to
edit YAM:REXX/TMS.yam  Just by looking at the script you should
see how to edit it. If not,. The line:

'C:TMS >NIL: "YAM:.taglines" "YAM:.signature" "9" "<sb>"'

Is how you would specify TMS from @{"CLI" link "M10"}.
And you should edit it the way you would type it in the CLI.

If you are using the multi tag script, then you will need
to edit the 3 lines.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "I01" "Installation Method 1"

I·N·S·T·A·L·L·A·T·I·O·N··M·E·T·H·O·D··1
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This way will add a tagline to just one signature file.

 o Use install script.
 o Open YAM, Open Preferences and goto the `ARexx' section.
 o Select `Before writing a message'.
 o Make sure AREXX is selected in the cycle gadget.
 o Click the File_Open gadget and find the REXX/TMS.yam
   script.
 o Save.

Then you should have a random tagline in your sig if everything
goes ok :).. And you have edited the @{"scripts" link "I00"} correctly.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "I02" "Installation Method 2"

I·N·S·T·A·L·L·A·T·I·O·N··M·E·T·H·O·D··2
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This way will add a tagline to your signature file. And the
2 alternatives.

 o Use install script.
 o Open YAM, Open Preferences and goto the `ARexx' section.
 o Select `Before writing a message'.
 o Make sure AREXX is selected in the cycle gadget.
 o Click the File_Open gadget and find the REXX/MULTI_TMS.yam
   script.
 o Save.

Then you should have a random tagline in your 3 sigs everytime
you write a new message. Ff everything goes ok :)..
And you have edited the @{"scripts" link "I00"} correctly.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "I03" "Installation Method 3"

I·N·S·T·A·L·L·A·T·I·O·N··M·E·T·H·O·D··3
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
If for whatever reason, you are unable to use AREXX scripts,
(RexxMast not working properly or whatever), or you cant edit
the scripts for whatever reason. There is this 1 last way
you can use TMS. Which is to use the Change_TagLine program
in the main TMS/ directory.

U·S·I·N·G··C·H·A·N·G·E··T·A·G·L·I·N·E
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
It is a WB Program, and it is designed to quickly execute
the TMS program. And make it function my TOOLTYPES.

Firstly edit the IconFile, and change the tooltypes.
These are the same as the @{"CLI" link "M10"} version parenthesis.

Then you can either run Change_Tagline whenever you want to,
or create as script something like the one below to start
Change_Tagline before YAM.

; AmigaDOS Script for TMS.

Work:TMS/Change_Tagline
YAM:YAM

; End script.

@ENDNODE

